sions: Our measurement has allowed to determine the $^{14}$N(n,p)\ncross-section over a wide energy range for the first time. We have obtained\ncross-sections with high accuracy (2.5 %) from sub-thermal energy to 800 keV\nand used these data to calculate the MACS for kT = 5 to kT = 100 keV.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 9 Dec 2022 22:06:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-13"}
